ev.content: I'm writing a Nostr client. Users can log in. What is the approach to select which relays first to connect to? Is it via user metadata, NIP-65 or just hardcode the top 10 relays and call it a day?

msg.content: I think that NIP-65 (kind 10002) is the best approach. Then, if the user doesn't have metadata, a "default relay" set (top 5 or 6)

Thanks man! I just wanted to make sure before I lost my sanity because most web clients basically hardcode a bunch of relays. I have enough 10002s and they still insist with the damn relays they choose. Coracle (after I reported the bug) started to work a bit better
I ended up doing what you suggest, with the addition of checking NIP-05 relays before using defaults
